<br>
now the story. a group is formed at zone while only 8 people in OS. and a very good group at that. 59 warr, 58 warr, 57 sk, 58 rog (me), 53 cle, 55 chanter (sejal). we decide to go to crypt asumeing we will fly by it and will have no prob with the emp. our first round goes great, we clear the crypt, blood, and emp ph and had time to go to crypt and take out another 9 mobs or so. 2 nd goes just as fast but this time we have the emp up )   emp fiight goes very clean exept near the end Sejal gets agros and holds it for around 15 seconds. (now i dont play a cle so dont know how hard it is to keep an enc alive for that long but am guessing it isnt easy). Sejal falls we kill emp and get a couple spells and dw arms. after res we head back to crypt and wiat for the ICG's'. this is where Sejal starts playing the blame game and saying the cleric was slacking off/sucked. considering the situation and that our cle was doing a good job i disagreed. i said this in group that it wasnt the clerics fault, people die on emp sometimes, it happens. the rest of the group said similar comments and this aperently was too much for our whineing enc to handle. at this point ICG one is half dead and #2 is mezed. Sejal says &quot;good luck without me&quot;, disbands and gates. mez breaks we try to off tank but not good on ICGm cle dies, main warr dies, the rest of us try to run but make it to necro and fall there. CR was a pain and we were not to happy.<br>
<br>
sorry for the long rant but i feel it is necisary as a warning to all. and Crimson Eternity you might want to keep an eye on your Probie Sejal. i remember something on your page about loyalty and Honor i believe.<br>
<br>
<br>
Serryn<br>
