<br>
Chanters get aggro all the time. Usually it only takes a taunt to get it back on the tank, but sometimes mobs focus on them until they die. Chanter die fast, Tanks usually only get one pop of their taunt button to change aggro and they have to pray that is enough. <br>
<br>
It's the life of an enchanter. Sometimes they die. Sometimes pullers die. Sometimes tanks die. Sometimes characters die. At level 55 any character should be used to it happening even when everyone is doing their job perfectly. Especially chanters. In any given 6 person group, if only one of the characters is dead after a fight, 9 out of ten times it is the enchanter.<br>
<br>
At level 55, one death (with a res) is nothing unusual and shouldnt raise anyone's hackles. <br>
<br>
Gating away from a group in the middle of a fight where you are key, that is unforgivable.<br>
